cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a unified video and language pre-training model for multimodal understanding and generation. It combines techniques from natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) to create a model that can understand and generate captions for videos. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses a Transformer backbone, which is a popular deep learning architecture for language tasks, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, since the paper deals with multimodal tasks, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category.
